          <exercise id="3.6.ex4" level="basic"> <!-- Changed from general to basic -->
            <question><paragraph>4. If a compound has the formula <formula type="chemical">MgCl₂</formula>, what type of bonding would you expect between Mg and Cl? Write the electron configuration for each ion in this compound.</paragraph></question>
            <answer><paragraph><emphasis type="italic">Answer</emphasis>: Ionic bonding. Mg: [Ne] → <formula type="chemical">Mg²⁺</formula>: [Ne] (or 1s²2s²2p⁶); Cl: [Ne]3s²3p⁵ → <formula type="chemical">Cl⁻</formula>: [Ne]3s²3p⁶ or [Ar]</paragraph></answer>
