          <paragraph>2. The heaviest stable element on the periodic table (Bismuth, Z=83) has a molar mass about 200 times greater than hydrogen, but one mole of each still contains exactly the same number of atoms.</paragraph>
        </content>
        <content type="fun_fact_item" id="4.7.ff3">
          <paragraph>3. Mole Day is celebrated by chemists on October 23 (10/23) from 6:02 AM to 6:02 PM, representing the digits in Avogadro's number (<formula type="math">6.022 × 10²³</formula>).</paragraph>
        </content>
