          <exercise id="6.3.ex3" level="intermediate">
            <question><paragraph>3. An inorganic chemist places one mole of <formula type="chemical">PCl₅</formula> in container A and one mole of each <formula type="chemical">Cl₂</formula> and <formula type="chemical">PCl₃</formula> in container B. Both containers were sealed and heated to the same temperature to reach the state of equilibrium. Guess about the composition of mixtures in both the containers.</paragraph>
