           <exercise id="6.3.ex4" level="intermediate">
            <question><paragraph>4. CaO or lime is used extensively in steel, glass and paper industries. It is produced in an endothermic (corrected from exothermic in source) reversible reaction by the decomposition of limestone (<formula type="chemical">CaCO₃</formula>). Choose the conditions to produce maximum amount of lime: <formula type="chemical">CaCO₃(s) ⇌ CaO(s) + CO₂(g)</formula>.</paragraph>
