            <answer><paragraph><emphasis type="italic">Answer</emphasis>: Mineral acids typically ionize completely or to a much larger extent in water, producing a higher concentration of H+ (or H₃O⁺) ions compared to natural (organic) acids, which often ionize only partially.</paragraph></answer>
          </exercise>
