                <item>b) Sodium with chlorine</item>
                <item>c) Lithium with water</item>
              </list>
            </question>
            <answer>
              <paragraph><emphasis type="italic">Answers</emphasis>:</paragraph>
              <paragraph>a) <formula type="chemical">4K(s) + O₂(g) → 2K₂O(s)</formula> (Potassium can also form peroxide <formula type="chemical">K₂O₂</formula> and superoxide <formula type="chemical">KO₂</formula> more readily than K₂O with excess oxygen)</paragraph>
