            <answer><paragraph><emphasis type="italic">Answer</emphasis>: Vanadium pentoxide is less susceptible to poisoning by impurities (like arsenic compounds often found in sulfur sources) compared to platinum. It is also generally more cost-effective for this large-scale industrial process.</paragraph></answer>
          </exercise>
