            <question><paragraph>3. What property of transition metals allows them to have high tensile strength, making them useful in construction?</paragraph></question>
            <answer><paragraph><emphasis type="italic">Answer</emphasis>: Strong metallic bonding involving delocalized s and d electrons contributes to their high tensile strength (resistance to breaking under tension).</paragraph></answer>
          </exercise>
          <exercise id="9.3.ex4" level="intermediate"> <!-- Changed from general to intermediate -->
