          <exercise id="11.3.ex3" level="advanced"> <!-- Changed from mechanism_analysis to advanced -->
            <question><paragraph>3. Describe the type of reaction involved in the hydrogenation of an alkyne to an alkane. Is it an addition, substitution, elimination, or rearrangement reaction? Explain.</paragraph></question>
            <answer><paragraph><emphasis type="italic">Answer</emphasis>: It is an addition reaction. Hydrogen atoms are added across the carbon-carbon triple bond (and subsequently the double bond intermediate), breaking the pi bonds and forming new C-H sigma bonds, without any atoms being removed from the original alkyne molecule.</paragraph></answer>
